  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through legitimate businesses or financial systems. Key elements typically include:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into financial systems\n2. Layering: Concealing the source through complex transactions\n3. Integration: Reintroducing the money into the economy as seemingly legitimate funds\n\nLegal definitions vary by jurisdiction, but usually involve intentional attempts to hide the origins of money obtained through criminal activities.",
